====================================================================== 
1) Affected Software 

* RealPlayer SP 1.0.5

NOTE: Other versions may also be affected.

====================================================================== 
2) Severity 

Rating: Highly critical
Impact: System compromise
Where:  Remote

====================================================================== 
3) Vendor's Description of Software 

"RealPlayer SP lets you download video from thousands of Websites ï¿½ 
free! Just click on the "download this video" button above the video 
you want. It's just that easy. Now you can watch your favorite videos 
anywhere, anytime."

Product Link:
http://www.real.com/realplayer/

====================================================================== 
4) Description of Vulnerability

Secunia Research has discovered a vulnerability in RealPlayer SP, 
which can be exploited by malicious people to compromise a user's 
system.

The vulnerability is caused by missing input validation in the 
handling of sample chunks when parsing QCP audio content. This can be 
exploited to cause a heap-based buffer overflow.

Successful exploitation may allow execution of arbitrary code.

====================================================================== 
5) Solution 

Update to RealPlayer SP 1.1.5 or RealPlayer Enterprise 2.1.3.

====================================================================== 
6) Time Table 

25/02/2010 - Vendor notified.
11/03/2010 - Vendor provides status update.
17/08/2010 - Vendor provides status update.
30/09/2010 - Vendor provides status update.
08/10/2010 - Vendor provides status update.
18/10/2010 - Public disclosure.

